pendix:Glossary\">accusative</a></span><span about=\"#mwt96\">]</span>"}]},{"partOfSpeech":"Conjunction","language":"Faroese","definitions":[{"definition":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/whether\" title=\"whether\">whether</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/if\" title=\"if\">if</a>"}]}],"gl":[{"partOfSpeech":"Numeral","language":"Galician","definitions":[{"definition":"<span class=\"mw-empty-elt\" about=\"#mwt105\" typeof=\"mw:Transclusion\"><link rel=\"mw:PageProp/Category\" href=\"./Category:Galician_cardinal_numbers#UM\"></span> <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/one\" title=\"one\">one</a>"}]}],"de":[{"partOfSpeech":"Preposition","language":"German","definitions":[{"definition":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/about\" title=\"about\">about</a>","parsedExamples":[{"example":"Es geht <b>um</b> den Kuchen.","translation":"It's about the pie."}],"examples":["Es geht <b>um</b> den Kuchen."]},{"definition":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/around\" title=\"around\">around</a>","parsedExamples":[{"example":"<b>Um</b> die Ecke","translation":"around the corner"}],"examples":["<b>Um</b> die Ecke"]},{"definition":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/at\" title=\"at\">at</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/by\" title=\"by\">by</a>","parsedExamples":[{"example":"<b>Um</b> acht Uhr reisen wir ab","translation":"At eight o’clock we depart"}],"examples":["<b>Um</b> acht Uhr reisen wir ab"]},{"definition":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/by\" title=\"by\">by</a>","parsedExamples":[{"example":"Die Verkaufsmengen gingen <b>um</b> 6<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\">%</span> zurück.","translation":"Sales in volume has decreased by 6%."}],"examples":["Die Verkaufsmengen gingen <b>um</b> 6<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\">%</span> zurück."]},{"definition":"<span class=\"usage-label-sense\" about=\"#mwt146\" typeof=\"mw:Transclusion\"></span> <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/for\" title=\"for\">for</a>","parsedExamples":[{"example":"<b>Um</b> einen Euro bekommt man heute nicht besonders viel.","translation":"You can't buy much for one euro these days."},{"example":"Heute im Sonderangebot <b>um</b> nur 99 Euro.","translation":"Special offer today for only 99 euros."}],"examples":["<b>Um</b> einen Euro bekommt man heute nicht besonders viel.","Heute im Sonderangebot <b>um</b> nur 99 Euro."]}]},{"partOfSpeech":"Conjunction","language":"German","definitions":[{"definition":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/in_order_to\" title=\"in order to\">in order to</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/so_as_to\" title=\"so as to\">so as to</a>","parsedExamples":[{"example":"Wir sind gekommen, <b>um</b> zu helfen.","translation":"We’ve come (<b>in order</b>) <b>to</b> help."}],"examples":["Wir sind gekommen, <b>um</b> zu helfen."]}]},{"partOfSpeech":"Adjective","language":"German","definitions":[{"definition":"<span class=\"usage-label-sense\" about=\"#mwt158\" typeof=\"mw:Transclusion\"></span> up, in the sense of finished","parsedExamples":[{"example":"Werden dich in kurzem binden<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\">/</span> <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink/Interwiki\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erdgeist\" title=\"w:Erdgeist\" class=\"extiw\">Erdgeist</a>, deine Zeit ist <b>um</b>","translation":"We will shortly bind you/ Erdgeist, your time is up","source":"Friedrich von Hardenberg, <i>Novalis</i>"}],"examples":["Werden dich in kurzem binden<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\">/</span> <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink/Interwiki\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erdgeist\" title=\"w:Erdgeist\" class=\"extiw\">Erdgeist</a>, deine Zeit ist <b>um</b>"]}]},{"partOfSpeech":"Adverb","language":"German","definitions":[{"definition":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/around\" title=\"around\">around</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/about\" title=\"about\">about</a>"},{"definition":"turned over, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/changed\" title=\"changed\">changed</a>, from one state to another"}]}],"is":[{"partOfSpeech":"Adverb","language":"Icelandic","definitions":[{"definition":"<span class=\"use-with-mention\" about=\"#mwt185\" typeof=\"mw:Transclusion\">used in set phrases</span>","parsedExamples":[{"example":"Það er <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/um_að_gera#Icelandic\" title=\"um að gera\"><b>um</b> að gera</a> að sofa vel.","translation":"The important thing to do is to sleep well."},{"example":"Hvað er <b>um</b> að vera<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\">?</span>","translation":"What's going on?"},{"example":"Eins og <b>um</b> var talað.","translation":"As was agreed."}],"examples":["Það er <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/um_að_gera#Icelandic\" title=\"um að gera\"><b>um</b> að gera</a> að sofa vel.","Hvað er <b>um</b> að vera<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\">?</span>","Eins og <b>um</b> var talað."]}]},{"partOfSpeech":"Preposition","language":"Icelandic","definitions":[{"definition":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/about\" title=\"about\">about</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/concerning\" title=\"concerning\">concerning</a>","parsedExamples":[{"example":"<b>Um</b> hvað ertu að tala<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\">?</span>","translation":"What are you talking <b>about</b>?"},{"example":"Spurning <b>um</b> líf og dauða.","translation":"A question <b>of</b> life and death."}],"examples":["<b>Um</b> hvað ertu að tala<span typeof=\"mw:Entity\">?</span>","Spurning <b>um</b> líf og dauða."]},{"definition":"<a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/through\" title=\"through\">through</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/around\" title=\"around\">around</a>, <a rel=\"mw:WikiLink\" href=\"/wiki/across\" title=\"across\">across</a>","parsedExamples":[{"example":"Áin rennur <b>um</b> dalinn.","translation":"The river runs <b>through</b> the valley."},{"example":"Að fara út <b>um</b> gluggann.","translation":"To go out <b>through</b> the window."},{"example":"Vestur <b>um</b> haf.","translation":"West <b>across</b> the sea."}],"examples":["Áin rennur <b>um</b> dalinn.","Að fara út <b>um</b> gluggann.","Vestur <b>um</b> haf."]},{